Permissions for: <account1>:role/srini-nonroot-role
This file allows the primary account to assume the role it needs to deploy
<account1>:role/srini-nonroot-role: allow the role to assume role to itself
<account2>:role/ROL-Spinnaker-Managed-Role: target-account role

USER: user/srini-nonroot. This user, MUST have these permissions as well
==================================================
PERMISSIONS (Policies)
ReadOnlyAccess
IAMReadOnlyAccess
and...this policy
==================================================

{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Action": "sts:AssumeRole",
            "Resource": [
                "arn:aws:iam::<account1>:role/srini-nonroot-role",    
                "arn:aws:iam::<account2>:role/ROL-Spinnaker-Managed-Role"
            ],
            "Effect": "Allow"
        }
    ]
}


==================================================
TRUST RELATIONSHIPS - Trust the USER "srini-nonroot"
This is only required if we outside the AWS Eco system
From EKS, change this to the role to trust
==================================================
{
  "Version": "2008-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<account1>:user/srini-nonroot"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
